(json 50 (proposer_id "28"))
(json 50 (title "Expand DeepFunding Town Hall to Africa &amp; LATAM"))
(json 50 (content "<p>The collaborative network between Swarm, Wada, and the Cardano Latin America Community seeks to expand the DeepFunding Town Hall format to Latin American and African Cardano Communities. They aim to create a distributed network of town halls in the blockchain and AI space, promoting global solutions for beneficial AGI while reflecting local perspectives. By launching town halls in Africa and Latin America, they plan to connect Cardano Communities to SingularityNET's DeepFunding and increase global engagement and participation.</p>
<p>The project is divided into several milestones, including setting up initial resources, training community leaders, hosting Africa and Latin America DeepFunding Town Halls, and reflecting on the experience with recommendations. The total budget for this initiative is $9,500 in AGIX.</p>
<p>To mitigate risks of low participation, they plan to create marketing materials and promote DeepFunding within the communities. The Town Halls will be free and open to the DeepFunding Community, with transparency and open-source principles guiding the project.</p>"))
(json 50 (link "https://deepfunding.ai/proposal/expand-deepfunding-town-hall-to-africa-latam/"))
(json 50 (feature_image "https://deepfunding.ai/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4-2.png"))
