(json 61 (title "Simulating a Risky World"))
(json 61 (content "<p>Photrek plans to develop Simulating Risky Worlds, a service for simulating virtual worlds with controllable uncertainty and relative risk levels. This service combines two components: Photrek's Risk-Aware Data Generator and Deep Brain's Open-Source World Models. They've secured $49,480 in funding to address the issue of brittle AI/ML algorithms, making them more robust to deviations from training data.</p>
<p>The solution utilizes Coupled Variational Autoencoder (CVAE) and includes a Memory Module with a Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) for predictive simulations. They aim to demonstrate the utility of Simulating a Risky World to potential customers, including organizations like Vantage Risk and NOAA Severe Storm Laboratory.</p>
<p>The project will be divided into milestones, including integrating CVAE with Dynamics and onboarding Simulating a Risky World. Hosting costs will cover Google Cloud servers, Ethereum transaction fees, and AGIX fees.</p>
<p>Photrek intends to offer 2.5% of revenue when it exceeds $5,000 as support to SingularityNET. Their software will be open source, with various licensing models for different components.</p>"))
