(json 65 (title "AI4M: An AI Model that enhances predictability of malaria occurrence and outcomes across various demographics for proactive and targeted responses."))
(json 65 (content "<p>HIESMEDIC presents a groundbreaking initiative harnessing machine learning to create an AI model for accurately predicting malaria outbreaks and their impact on diverse population groups. This innovation includes a comprehensive database accessible through APIs, allowing integration with other predictive analysis systems for various communicable diseases. Malaria remains a significant global health challenge, and the lack of accurate predictability hampers targeted interventions. HIESMEDIC's AI4M Model aims to provide granular predictions by considering factors like environment, socio-economics, genetics, and healthcare access. Their marketing strategy includes targeting government health agencies, non-profits, healthcare providers, and research institutions. The project milestones involve data acquisition, model development, validation, integration, pilot implementation, regulatory compliance, scaling, monitoring, impact assessment, and market expansion. The budget breakdown ensures a structured approach to achieving their goals and making a meaningful impact in the fight against malaria.</p>"))
