(json 68 (title "HiveMind &#8211; augmented Q&amp;A bot and P2P knowledge base"))
(json 68 (content "<p>TogetherCrew and P2P Foundation propose collaborating with SingularityNET on the Community Memory-augmented LLMs - RFP 3. Their project, HiveMind, aims to empower communities by providing an LLM-powered chatbot that can answer questions by leveraging dispersed community knowledge. The system bridges various platforms (Discord, Discourse, GitHub, Google Drive, and Notion) to answer loosely structured questions and specific queries about community documentation. They have partnered with the P2P Foundation to pilot HiveMind using their unique knowledge base of research and articles on P2P and Commons.</p>
<p>The requested funding amount is $72,000, allocated across ten milestones that include data collection, system development, API creation, security enhancements, and marketplace integration. They address potential risks related to accuracy, GDPR compliance, team capacity, code quality, usability, data aggregation, security, privacy, and project management.</p>
<p>TogetherCrew and P2P Foundation aim to improve community collaboration and knowledge accessibility through HiveMind, aligning with SingularityNET's mission for a more compassionate, just, and sustainable world.</p>"))
(json 68 (link "https://deepfunding.ai/proposal/hivemind-augmented-qa-bot-and-p2p-knowledge-base/"))
(json 68 (feature_image "https://deepfunding.ai/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/5.jpeg"))
