(json 71 (title "Community Engagement Scores"))
(json 71 (content "<p>Photrek's proposal for RFP1: Community Engagement Score - Part 2 aims to enhance the community decision-making processes within SingularityNET's Deep Funding program by developing a Community Engagement Score (CES). Building upon their successful proof of concept funded by Deep Fund 2 Tooling, Photrek plans to use $80,000 from Round 3 SingularityNET RFP funds to further develop the CES system. Their objectives include integrating additional requirements for final voting weights and rewards, ensuring alignment with academic literature and best practices, and exploring future functionalities like social metrics and knowledge graphs. Photrek's proposed timeline spans 6-8 months, focusing on creating a Minimum Viable Product (MVP), conducting research, extensive testing, and deployment. They aim to address issues related to decision-making efficiency, transparency, tracking, and calculation opacity in the SingularityNET community. The project reflects their commitment to improving user-driven decision-making in deep funding and the SingularityNET ecosystem.</p>"))
