(json 72 (title "Customizable Code Assistant"))
(json 72 (content "<p>This project addresses the accessibility gap in using and developing large language models (LLMs) by making them more usable and reducing computational costs. The aim is to democratize LLMs' practicality by exploring transfer learning on small pre-trained models for new programming languages and tasks. The solution entails generating datasets, conducting performance-cost analysis, fine-tuning and evaluating models, creating GPU inference environments, and deploying a modular pipeline for customizable Code Assistants. The budget of $30,000 covers these milestones. Risks are mitigated through privacy measures, licensing compliance, and adapting to computation costs. The project's inspiration stems from previous collaborative work and aims to contribute to AI's democratization through accessible and open-source models and datasets.</p>"))
